<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 11:41PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHEASTERN JUNIATA AND
NORTHEASTERN PERRY COUNTIES THROUGH 1215 AM EDT...
At 1141 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Lewistown, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mcalisterville, Spruce Hill, Mexico, Ickesburg, Mifflintown, Port
Royal, Thompsontown, Millerstown, Mifflin and East Salem.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
